Package: funcml
Type: Package
Title: Machine Learning Framework for R
Version: 0.7.1
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Imad", family = "El Badisy", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "elbadisyimad@gmail.com")
  )
Author: Imad El Badisy [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Imad El Badisy <elbadisyimad@gmail.com>
Description: Machine learning framework for R.
    Provides a compact and explicit framework for supervised learning,
    resampling-based evaluation, hyperparameter tuning, learner comparison,
    interpretation, and plug-in g-computation through stable S3 interfaces and
    a learner registry covering multiple backend engines. Model
    specification uses standard R formulas within a broader framework for
    fitting, evaluation, tuning, interpretation, and causal estimation. The
    package is intentionally opinionated:
    preprocessing is expected to happen outside the modeling step, and the
    framework emphasizes explicit inputs, consistent object contracts, and a
    compact API rather than competing feature for feature with larger
    machine learning ecosystems.
